00:35.536 --> 00:37.671
[Boy]
They say the last thing
she cried out

00:37.705 --> 00:40.108
As they put the noose
around her neck,

00:41.742 --> 00:44.845
Was a curse
on all the children
of the land.

00:44.878 --> 00:47.348
Don't they usually
burn witches?

00:47.381 --> 00:49.783
She wasn't like
any other witch.

00:49.817 --> 00:52.453
She wouldn't drown.

00:52.486 --> 00:55.089
She wouldn't burn.

00:55.123 --> 00:59.427
It took nine hours
before she finally died.

00:59.460 --> 01:02.263
They took her down
and cut up her body

01:02.296 --> 01:06.234
And placed it
in nine unmarked graves.

01:08.402 --> 01:12.306
My granddad says
witches don't exist.

01:12.340 --> 01:15.376
Of course they do.
My dad was there.

01:15.409 --> 01:18.179
He saw
the hanging.

01:18.212 --> 01:22.450
Blood leaked
from her eyes.

01:22.483 --> 01:24.352
The children
didn't get sick

01:24.385 --> 01:27.388
When they played
around the tree.

01:27.421 --> 01:30.158
People are saying
that Aldric has got plague.

01:30.191 --> 01:33.194
His sister said
he was always playing
around the hanging tree.

01:34.628 --> 01:36.597
She searches out
other children

01:36.630 --> 01:39.700
Just like
her only son, Ulric.

01:39.733 --> 01:43.404
Did she really
murder him?
Yes.

01:43.437 --> 01:47.441
She took her son
while he was sleeping.

01:47.475 --> 01:49.210
At St. Jonas' farm.

01:51.245 --> 01:54.182
She slit
his throat open.

01:56.584 --> 01:57.685
Along with the pigs.

02:01.422 --> 02:05.626
They say you can still
hear him crying through
the trees.

02:11.932 --> 02:14.235
Trying to ward off
other children,

02:14.268 --> 02:17.137
She wants to play
with her son.

02:19.807 --> 02:21.509
There's only one way
to find out

02:21.542 --> 02:24.745
If what they say
about Isobel is true.

02:24.778 --> 02:27.515
We must put our sticks
in the fire,

02:27.548 --> 02:31.352
And whoever's
burns up the quickest,

02:31.385 --> 02:33.821
Must touch
the witching tree.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.156
[Woman]
I must say,
Mrs. Thorson,

04:16.189 --> 04:19.293
I was quite surprised
to hear that you wanted
to go ahead with it

04:19.327 --> 04:21.862
After everything
that's happened.

04:21.894 --> 04:23.964
It's what Tony
would've wanted.

04:27.034 --> 04:28.502
For me to have gone
through with it.

04:31.539 --> 04:33.741
Well, I think
it's a very brave
decision.

04:33.774 --> 04:36.777
Have you heard anymore
from the hospital?

04:36.810 --> 04:39.347
No.

04:39.380 --> 04:41.549
But he's going
to get better.

04:43.116 --> 04:45.619
Yeah.
Yeah, absolutely.

04:47.555 --> 04:50.324
You know, I grew up
not far from here,

04:50.358 --> 04:53.927
And... well, to me,
St. Jonas' farm

04:53.961 --> 04:56.830
Always had something

04:56.864 --> 04:58.899
Of the heavens
about it.

05:02.002 --> 05:04.372
It's not so bad
for an 800-year
old house, is it?

05:04.405 --> 05:05.706
It's done quite well.

05:08.909 --> 05:10.644
Anyway,
I think you
and your family

05:10.678 --> 05:12.012
Are going to be
very happy here.

05:12.045 --> 05:14.014
[Birds chirping]

05:16.550 --> 05:19.553
I've left some tea bags
on the counter for you.

05:19.587 --> 05:21.555
And...

05:21.589 --> 05:23.591
Don't believe the things
you hear about Isobel.

05:23.624 --> 05:25.793
And there's milk
in the fridge.

05:25.826 --> 05:27.361
What?

05:28.962 --> 05:30.564
Milk.

05:30.598 --> 05:32.433
There's milk
in the fridge

05:32.466 --> 05:34.334
If you wanted
to make yourself
a cup of tea.

05:38.105 --> 05:39.640
Thank you.

05:53.053 --> 05:55.756
It's a healing stone.

05:55.789 --> 05:58.358
It's meant
to be stronger
than some doctors.

06:01.595 --> 06:03.631
I take it
Mom has told you
about the farm.

06:05.999 --> 06:09.470
Why did you decide
to live on a farm
when you were kids?

06:09.503 --> 06:12.440
It's all right for you.
You're in a fucking coma.

06:14.975 --> 06:17.778
Come on.
You know you want
to wake up and ground me.

06:17.811 --> 06:20.914
It's the "F" word.

06:20.948 --> 06:22.650
(Emma)
Jake.

06:22.683 --> 06:25.953
I knew you'd be here.
What are you doing?

06:25.986 --> 06:28.689
Trying to get Dad
to wake up and ground me.

06:28.722 --> 06:31.892
You're lucky
I got home before Mom.

06:31.925 --> 06:33.627
She finds that
you're bunking again

06:33.661 --> 06:36.797
And I'm covering up for you,
she'll kill us both.

06:36.830 --> 06:39.132
Dad's not waking up
anytime soon to stop her.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.636
I cannot be
bothered with today.

06:42.670 --> 06:45.105
Is it the same lads?
No.

06:45.138 --> 06:47.040
They don't bloody
bother me anymore.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.743
Don't swear.
"Bloody" isn't swearing.

06:49.777 --> 06:52.680
Yeah, it is.
And how come Mr. Henderson
is always saying it

06:52.713 --> 06:54.181
When shouting at me
for bunking?

06:54.214 --> 06:56.784
'Cause Mr. Henderson
is a dick.

06:56.817 --> 06:59.853
Look, go away outside.

07:03.691 --> 07:05.125
See you
on Thursday, Dad.

07:11.732 --> 07:13.834
Hi, Dad.

07:13.867 --> 07:16.670
Mom really is losing it
without you, you know?

07:19.607 --> 07:21.542
If you don't
wake up soon...

07:27.080 --> 07:29.983
I'll bring you some
new flowers from the farm
when we move in.

08:05.953 --> 08:07.521
[Door opens]

08:13.226 --> 08:15.095
So, what
do you think?

08:15.128 --> 08:17.030
I think,

08:17.064 --> 08:19.066
When did we become
Dickens children?

08:19.099 --> 08:21.769
Does it have heating?
Oh, don't start.

08:21.802 --> 08:24.638
You've got much
bigger bedrooms here
than in the last place.

08:24.672 --> 08:26.840
Why?
The animals aren't sleeping
with us, are they?

08:26.874 --> 08:29.677
We don't do the whole
nativity look, Mom.

08:29.710 --> 08:32.980
No, because the last holiday
we had, I couldn't even
get you in a barn.

09:07.848 --> 09:10.618
I've decided I want
to become a vegetarian.
Like Emma.

09:14.187 --> 09:16.256
You don't want
to be a vegetarian
like Emma.

09:16.289 --> 09:18.992
You just want
to wind me up.

09:19.026 --> 09:21.294
Now, finish
your lamb.

09:21.328 --> 09:23.063
I don't want to eat
Shawn the Sheep.

09:23.096 --> 09:24.932
It's not Shawn
the Sheep.

09:24.965 --> 09:27.735
It's off from a TV contract
from Wallace and Gromit.

09:27.768 --> 09:30.871
That sheep was killed
and put in the plate
for you to eat.

09:30.904 --> 09:33.774
How come Emma's allowed
to be a vegetarian
and I'm not?

09:33.807 --> 09:37.678
Because Emma decided to become
a vegetarian before we moved
to the farm,

09:37.711 --> 09:40.180
And before she was trying
to make a statement about it.

09:40.213 --> 09:43.951
Well, I'm not hungry then.
You've been unpacking all day.
How can you not be hungry?

09:45.252 --> 09:48.155
I'm not.
Fine, fine.

09:48.188 --> 09:50.023
Then feed the rest
to the pigs and get to bed.

09:52.159 --> 09:54.027
Not from the plate.

09:54.061 --> 09:55.796
It'll make
the washing up easier.

10:02.302 --> 10:04.371
He's getting worse
than you.

10:04.404 --> 10:06.239
Maybe if you don't make
the meat so rare and bloody,

10:06.273 --> 10:08.909
It might not
put him off so much.

10:08.942 --> 10:11.244
That's how
I've always cooked it.

10:11.278 --> 10:14.347
Yeah, and you've
already got one daughter
who's a vegetarian.

10:14.381 --> 10:16.850
Maybe take the hint.

10:16.884 --> 10:20.120
He's already started
naming the animals.

10:20.153 --> 10:22.222
I told him
not to do that.

10:22.255 --> 10:26.193
Yeah, well, I suggest
you make sure he doesn't name
any of them Shawn.

10:40.373 --> 10:42.242
"Happy moving in."

10:42.275 --> 10:44.244
* You're making me

10:44.277 --> 10:47.981
* Making me
A Monster *

10:48.015 --> 10:51.051
* Oh can't you see
Oh can't you see *

10:51.084 --> 10:52.920
[Voice whispers]

10:55.856 --> 10:58.892
* Oh you're making me
You're making me *

10:58.926 --> 11:02.095
* You're making me
A Monster *

11:04.331 --> 11:06.734
* [Vocalizing]

11:15.442 --> 11:18.178
I've given you a checklist
of things to do.

11:18.211 --> 11:20.413
Have you included
point 22, killing myself?

11:20.447 --> 11:23.216
You'll enjoy it
once you get used to it.
Why?

11:23.250 --> 11:25.385
Have you agreed
to start paying me
ten pounds an hour?

11:25.418 --> 11:28.055
You help here
on the farm,
you get free rent.

11:28.088 --> 11:30.157
So, as I'm technically
paying rent,

11:30.190 --> 11:32.425
Does that mean
I can have boys over?

11:32.459 --> 11:34.895
Possibly.

11:34.928 --> 11:37.297
Except for Mike.

11:37.330 --> 11:41.434
Look, I'm the landlord,
I set the terms.

11:41.468 --> 11:45.873
Speaking of pigs,
let's get you introduced.

11:47.274 --> 11:48.809
[Crows cawing]

12:14.267 --> 12:17.237
[Guy]
Where did he go?
Come back here.

12:17.270 --> 12:19.773
Why do you want to be
in a coma like your dad?

12:40.894 --> 12:42.095
Ow.

13:30.310 --> 13:32.079
What are you sketching?

13:32.112 --> 13:33.947
Nothing.

13:37.184 --> 13:39.019
The pigs keep on
making funny noises.

13:41.554 --> 13:44.257
They're just getting used
to their new home.

13:44.291 --> 13:46.159
Like we are.

13:52.966 --> 13:54.868
[Cell phone vibrating]

14:34.074 --> 14:35.909
Seriously,
if your mom...
My mom what?

14:35.943 --> 14:39.212
Look, she's got a farm now,
and she's got a shotgun.

14:39.246 --> 14:41.614
So... you're my naughty.

14:41.648 --> 14:42.916
Naughty rabbit.

14:44.617 --> 14:47.054
I love it when you do
the Emma-fucked-over thing.

14:47.087 --> 14:49.222
[Bed creaks]

15:03.570 --> 15:05.138
Jake?

15:08.341 --> 15:09.342
[Mom]
Emma?

15:12.612 --> 15:13.981
What is it?

15:19.987 --> 15:21.955
Thought I heard voices.

15:21.989 --> 15:24.257
Maybe it was Jake.

15:24.291 --> 15:26.960
No, I've just checked him.

15:28.761 --> 15:31.598
You have been drinking.
Maybe it's the voices
in your head.

15:40.540 --> 15:42.442
[Panting]

15:44.577 --> 15:46.146
There was something
in there.

15:53.120 --> 15:55.355
Yeah.
You.

15:55.388 --> 15:57.224
Why do you always have
to have such a problem
with him?

15:57.257 --> 16:00.693
It's because Dad's
not here to approve?

16:00.727 --> 16:03.263
I just found him
in your bedroom
with his trousers down.

16:03.296 --> 16:06.366
You would at least let him
put them back on before you
threw him out the front door.

16:06.399 --> 16:09.769
He was expelled
from school for having weed.
Oh, that was ages ago.
He was 15.

16:09.802 --> 16:12.172
That makes it worse.
He was set up.

16:12.205 --> 16:14.274
By the teacher's
little league wee club?

16:14.307 --> 16:17.044
Yeah, I thought they always
seemed a bit high that
Paris evening.

16:17.077 --> 16:18.178
Don't try
to be funny, Mom.
It's embarrassing.

16:18.211 --> 16:20.147
He's an idiot.
He's a cute idiot.

16:20.180 --> 16:22.382
Do you want
to end up like me?
Pregnant at 16?

16:22.415 --> 16:24.384
I was such a big
fucking mistake, was I?

16:24.417 --> 16:26.586
He's not having
his trousers down again
with you in my house.

16:26.619 --> 16:29.522
Fine. I'll invite him out
for random nudity when I'm out.

16:29.556 --> 16:31.691
God, sometimes I wish
I was religious like Dad,

16:31.724 --> 16:33.693
Because then I could go
into confession and tell them
I'm guilty

16:33.726 --> 16:35.295
Of thinking my mom
is a bitch.

16:44.404 --> 16:46.073
[Door slams]

17:11.364 --> 17:12.464
[Male voice]
Emma.

17:17.503 --> 17:19.239
Dad?

17:58.678 --> 18:00.547
[Kid's voice
whispering]
Isobel.

18:17.530 --> 18:19.132
[Gasps]

18:20.233 --> 18:21.168
[Exhales]

18:22.702 --> 18:24.337
Jake.

18:36.716 --> 18:39.286
Hey, guys.

18:39.319 --> 18:41.254
How are you?

18:41.288 --> 18:44.824
Dad still
hasn't woken up.

18:44.857 --> 18:47.227
Mom and Emma
have been fighting again.

18:48.661 --> 18:50.330
Can't even taste
the bacon.

18:53.400 --> 18:55.802
Have you not intended
to muck the pigs out
and that?

18:55.835 --> 18:58.705
Very funny.

18:58.738 --> 19:01.708
Caught Jake
sleepwalking again
last night.

19:01.741 --> 19:03.776
He hasn't done that
since Dad went
into the coma.

19:05.412 --> 19:08.215
He's just adjusting
to the new house.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.817
It'll stop
once we're settled in.

19:10.850 --> 19:14.821
I've got to get him off.
Make sure you get that
assignment done today.

19:14.854 --> 19:17.290
Is that before or after
I feed the pigs?

19:17.324 --> 19:19.559
Whichever you want
to conform to the most.

19:20.660 --> 19:21.828
Pigs.

19:21.861 --> 19:23.630
[Pigs grunting]

19:28.601 --> 19:30.903
Oh, God.
You guys eat more
than Uncle Johnny.

19:30.937 --> 19:34.241
[Pigs grunting]

19:46.253 --> 19:49.822
The esophagus was
probably torn, which would
have made it cough up blood.

19:49.856 --> 19:52.625
Did the pigs come
from the same litter?

19:52.659 --> 19:55.228
No, they were bred
by friends of my husband.

20:01.501 --> 20:03.436
It's a nice farm,
St. Jonas.

20:03.470 --> 20:05.238
A bit scary.

20:07.474 --> 20:08.275
I had heard.

20:11.043 --> 20:13.746
No, I meant,
have I taken on
too much?

20:13.780 --> 20:16.283
Yeah, of course.

20:16.316 --> 20:18.451
My dad used
to be the vet here.

20:18.485 --> 20:21.654
I've just taken on
the family business.

20:21.688 --> 20:24.957
He did say
the family before said
the house had a few problems.

20:27.026 --> 20:28.828
With-With the roof.

20:48.715 --> 20:50.950
[Shouting]
Stop, stop.

20:50.983 --> 20:52.018
No!

20:55.322 --> 20:58.057
I spoke
to the doctor again.

20:58.090 --> 21:01.461
You said that
you'd reconsider
after two weeks.

21:03.730 --> 21:06.466
Jake said he saw
his hand move.
Oh.

21:06.499 --> 21:10.737
Jake would say anything,
the same as you would.

21:10.770 --> 21:12.505
Tony would hate this.

21:12.539 --> 21:14.441
And how do you know
what Tony would want?

21:14.474 --> 21:17.444
I'm his mother.
And he's my husband.

21:17.477 --> 21:20.012
And he spoke to me
a hell of a lot more
than he spoke to you.

21:20.046 --> 21:22.949
And how much
do you speak
to your children now?

21:22.982 --> 21:26.085
Living in your
little world,

21:26.118 --> 21:30.457
Trying to create
this fantasy home
for him to come back to.

21:30.490 --> 21:32.359
He might.

21:32.392 --> 21:35.328
He would rather die
than come back like that.

21:37.897 --> 21:42.435
Oh.
It would be worse for him
than being in a coma.

21:42.469 --> 21:45.372
And if that
did happen,

21:45.405 --> 21:47.707
You wouldn't have the option
to switch him off.

21:49.876 --> 21:52.479
You've got
to let go, Amber.

21:52.512 --> 21:56.115
Those children
have got to let go.

21:56.148 --> 21:58.951
And if you can't do it
for you and Tony,

21:58.985 --> 22:00.587
Then do it
for Emma and Jake.

22:10.897 --> 22:12.799
Two more weeks.

22:13.966 --> 22:17.604
That is what
you always say.

22:22.909 --> 22:24.744
This time I mean it.

22:29.582 --> 22:32.552
Hey, you moved
into that new farm.
So?

22:32.585 --> 22:36.689
Only just moved in
and already smells
of pig shit.

22:36.723 --> 22:39.125
How much
did you pay for it?
I don't know.

22:39.158 --> 22:41.828
Probably got a good rate
considering what
happened there.

22:41.861 --> 22:43.129
Nothing happened there.

22:43.162 --> 22:45.998
You're calling
me a liar?
No.

22:46.032 --> 22:48.801
You know, if you want us
to stop picking on you,

22:48.835 --> 22:51.771
All you need to do
is show us that you're
all right.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.940
How can I be all right?
Do something.

22:53.973 --> 22:56.609
Like what?
I don't know.

22:56.643 --> 22:58.945
Find out
why that woman
murdered her family.

22:58.978 --> 23:00.913
No woman murdered...
Yes, she did.

23:00.947 --> 23:02.682
She was just
like your mom.

23:02.715 --> 23:05.618
And they moved in.
Just like your family did.

23:05.652 --> 23:08.955
She gave him sleeping pills
before going to sleep
and burnt him alive.

23:10.857 --> 23:13.993
Afterwards, the mom
hanged herself
in the barn.

23:14.026 --> 23:16.563
Still no one
knows why.

23:16.596 --> 23:19.899
But your mom will do
exactly the same thing
to you and your sister

23:19.932 --> 23:21.067
If you don't find out
in time.

23:21.100 --> 23:22.869
How am I going
to find that out?

23:22.902 --> 23:25.171
Tyler's big brother
is in something
not really kosher.

23:25.204 --> 23:26.939
Right, Tyler?
Yeah.

23:26.973 --> 23:29.576
Embarrassing kid.
Hey.

23:29.609 --> 23:32.011
And he's got one
of these Ouija boards
like in The Exorcist.

23:47.594 --> 23:49.562
You've come
to help me?

23:49.596 --> 23:51.798
Ma, are you
all right?

23:51.831 --> 23:53.833
Why are you all
covered in mud?

23:53.866 --> 23:55.635
I fell over.

24:08.615 --> 24:10.550
Were you and Nan
talking about Dad
again today?

24:12.852 --> 24:14.621
No, she's just dropped by
to let me know

24:14.654 --> 24:16.689
That apparently
she's become
the first female pope.

24:21.994 --> 24:23.963
I saw more letters
have come through
from the hospital.

24:25.632 --> 24:27.900
Still no signs
of improvement then?

24:31.137 --> 24:32.972
I hope you don't...
Um, bloody vegan,

24:33.005 --> 24:34.907
What am I meant
to put in these rolls?

24:38.711 --> 24:42.715
If you kids think...
Mom, I support you in whatever
you want to do with Dad.

24:42.749 --> 24:44.951
Jake is not ready
to let him go.

24:46.853 --> 24:50.690
What did you tell Nan?
Two weeks.

24:50.723 --> 24:52.859
How did she take that?

24:52.892 --> 24:55.261
Well, let's just say
your dad wasn't lying
when he said that your Nan

24:55.294 --> 24:57.530
Could breathe fire
like a dragon.

25:00.032 --> 25:01.100
[Gasps]

25:03.002 --> 25:05.705
What?

25:05.738 --> 25:08.040
I just saw
something outside.

25:25.157 --> 25:26.893
Jake.

25:44.611 --> 25:47.714
Mom is really letting you
go out in that?

25:47.747 --> 25:51.017
Luckily, mom had to go
to London early today,
so she won't see it.

25:52.852 --> 25:54.754
You'd better head off.

25:54.787 --> 25:58.057
I will do.
I'm taking my bike,
so I can leave later.

25:58.090 --> 26:00.927
Yeah, well,
I'm heading out after college,
so I'll be back later.

26:00.960 --> 26:03.630
You can microwave
yourself something
if you get hungry.

26:03.663 --> 26:05.197
[Music from TV]

26:05.231 --> 26:07.900
You need to watch
your sleepwalking, okay?

26:07.934 --> 26:10.870
Sleepwalking?
Yeah, we found you
outside last night.

26:10.903 --> 26:13.139
Where?
Barn.

26:13.172 --> 26:15.842
You weird child.

26:21.147 --> 26:23.582
Bet SpongeBoob
doesn't have to deal
with this shit.

26:26.719 --> 26:28.655
And you're sure
they won't be back
until later?

26:28.688 --> 26:31.858
No.
My mom's
in London.

26:31.891 --> 26:34.260
